# Docs Editorial Workflow

- All docs under `docs/` must have YAML frontmatter with at minimum: `id`, `title`, `status`, `stage`, `type`. Add `authority`, `last_updated`, and `depends_on` where useful.
- Before editing a doc, read its frontmatter `depends_on` list and check those files for conflicts.
- `docs/vision.md` owns canonical principles and strategic guardrails.
- `docs/prd-foundation.md` owns scope, workflow, object model, and MVP requirements.
- `docs/decisions.md` owns decision status. Update it first when a decision changes, then propagate.
- `docs/roadmap.md` owns sequencing and exit criteria.
- `docs/milestones/` contains outcome-based charters, not implementation runbooks, unless a milestone has explicitly crossed into implementation.
- `docs/ops/` explains how agent-facing docs and repo operations work; update it when the operating model changes.
- `docs/catalog.json` is the machine-readable index of all docs. Update it when adding or removing docs.
- `AGENTS.md` is the canonical prose repo contract. `agent-manifest.json`, `llms.txt`, and `CLAUDE.md` are compatibility companions and should stay pointer-oriented.
- Prefer cross-references over duplicating the same decision across multiple docs.
- When referencing a decision, use the stable ID in parentheses, e.g., `(D60)`, so agents can grep from any doc back to `docs/decisions.md`.
- Specs that implement or are governed by specific decisions should list them in a `## Governing decisions` section near the top.
- Agent-routing and index docs should expose stable sections for purpose, use-when, not-for, update-when, and machine contract.
- When routing guidance changes, update the prose entrypoint, the machine index, any affected `.cursor/rules/*.mdc`, and then run `bash scripts/validate-agent-docs.sh`.
- Raw provenance stays in `research-output/`. Mined findings go to `docs/research/`.
